Stenoma umbrinervis is a moth in the family Depressariidae. It was described by Edward Meyrick in 1930. It is found in Par√°, Brazil.The wingspan is about 17 mm. The forewings are whitish grey, all veins and the dorsal edge marked with violet-grey streaks and the costal edge and subcostal pale line tinged yellowish at the base. The hindwings are light grey.